data: David and Irene are double first cousins because each is related through their mother's family and also their father's family, the result of a brother and sister (Ben and Helen) having married another brother and sister (Hugh and Betty). For David and Irene, each has a mother who is an aunt by marriage of the other and a father who is an uncle by marriage of the other.
Half cousins are the children of two half siblings.
David and Lilian are half cousins because their fathers (Ben and James) are half brothers, their grandmother (Agatha) having divorced and remarried.
Step-cousins are either stepchildren of an individual's aunt or uncle or nieces and nephews of one's step-parent.
David and Mary are step-cousins because David's uncle (Charles) has become Mary's stepfather as a result of Mary's mother (Corinda) having divorced and remarried.
A cousin-in-law is the spouse of an individual's cousin or the cousin of one's spouse.
David and Eric are first cousins-in-law to each other because Eric's wife (Emma) is David's first cousin.

A term that specifies whether one individual is a cousin of another through the mother's side of the family (maternal) or the father's side (paternal). If the relationship is not equally paternal for both or equally maternal for both, then the paternal cousin of one is the maternal cousin of the other.

Emma and David are paternal first cousins (being related through their fathers). Emma is also Nicola's paternal first cousin (as related on Nicola's father's side), but Nicola is Emma's maternal first cousin (as related on Emma's mother's side). David and Nicola are not cousins to each other.

table-0156-77.caption: Season 4: 1995–1996
data: Vanessa and Mark return to Oakland after neither's summer was to their liking, and learn Geneva has become principal of the high school. Omar Gooding becomes a Series Regular.
Rehired as basketball coach, Mark takes advantage of Geneva's position as principal, but the other teacher's resent what they see as special treatment for him.
Geneva recruits a new instructor for the Reserve Officer Training Corps, her former boyfriend, Master Sergeant Ken.
Though she just failed her EMT test, Vanessa saves Mark's life after he falls and gets a concussion.
Nicole and her friend tease Tyler after he's scared of a horror movie, and dare him to camp out in a haunted house on Halloween. Vanessa goes on her first shift as an EMT.
Nicole breaks Mark's prized mug and lets Vanessa take the blame. Later, while playing a fantasy computer game, Nicole falls asleep and has a dream that teaches her the importance of honesty.
When the ancient plumbing system breaks down in the house, Vanessa and Geneva hire a plumber. But Mark chases away the plumber and insists on fixing the problem himself.
Mark unwillingly goes to clean out Grandpa Cooper's mountain cabin. Vanessa deals with an uncooperative powerboat.

Geneva becomes exasperated with everyone in the house treating her like a servant. So, she moves out with Nicole. Mark invites his inconsiderate friends Steve and Lydell to move in, causing Vanessa to move out.

Mark lets Vanessa to practice wrapping bandages on him. While wearing a shoulder brace, Mark meets his beautiful new neighbor, Monique. Before Mark can explain that he is not injured, Monique becomes sympathetic. Using the situation to his advantage, Mark asks her on a date. Meanwhile, Nicole insists on wearing hip-hop clothing to express her individuality.
Disgusted by its commercial aspects, Mark tries to instill the family with the true spirit of Christmas.
After he falls in love with a girl at school, her gang member brother harasses Earvin, and threatens him with a gun.
Mark invests in a co-worker's invention, a robotic suit designed to improve the wearer's golf skills.
Mark becomes a student guidance counselor and advises an egotistical football player. Vanessa babysits Nicole and allows her to slack off on her studies.
Mark coordinates a talent show as a fundraiser for the school's athletic department and is promised an appearance by Boyz II Men by a man posing as the group's attorney.
Mark is upset when he is unable to attend a show put on by The Harlem Globetrotters for the fifth time in his life.
Mark tries to end a rivalry with a coach from another high school basketball team. Vanessa uses Tyler to try to get a date with a man in a single parents' group.

Mark causes a lot of bad luck for himself and those around him when he buys a beautiful car that the previous owner claims is haunted. Vanessa finds out her new relationship isn't as serious as she thought.

Knuckleball Smith, one of Vanessa's patients at the retirement home, intends to sell his classic car to please his jealous elderly lover, Edna. Geneva is afraid she may face an obstacle to being named principal on a permanent basis.
After Geneva introduces Vanessa to a successful, handsome man, Mark does everything he can to sabotage the developing relationship.
Breaking Up is Hard to Do

Mark and Vanessa announce that they are dating. After their first fight, they decide that it would be better if they were just friends, but on subsequent dates with other people, each can only think about the other.

Despite wanting to marry Mark, Vanessa innocently has lunch with her former boyfriend. When Mark finds out, he frantically proposes marriage to her. Geneva directs a school play written by Nicole. This show Is put On a one Year Hitaus Until the Summer of 1997.

data: After Vanessa accepts Mark's marriage proposal, Mark looks for a deal on a ring he can afford. But there's a misunderstanding about the price—after he gives it to Vanessa.
When Geneva feels she's in the way of the newlyweds-to-be and makes plans to move out, Mark enlists the help of Tyler's rambunctious young relatives to convince her to stay.
Mark meets Vanessa's extremely wealthy parents for the first time, and hopes that they will pay for the wedding.

Vanessa's job working as an emergency medical technician is eliminated due to budget cuts, so she starts her own business selling African beauty supplies. Meanwhile, Mark takes an additional job at a security company.

Vanessa is very tense from planning her wedding, so her friend Florence invites her to a spa for relaxation. Mark becomes jealous when he realizes that the spa is staffed by attractive men who are eager to please their customers.
Tyler makes a date with a girl for his first school dance, but Mark gives him bad advice on how to treat women.
When Mark argues with the high school's girls' basketball coach, they decide to settle their differences with a one-on-one basketball game. Tyler and Nicole need blood samples for science class.
To help the school earn money for textbooks, Mark works at a carnival pretending to be a fortuneteller.
Mark and Vanessa get into an argument, but they both have conflicting viewpoints as to what really happened.
Vanessa pressures Geneva's longtime boyfriend, Ken, into asking Geneva to marry him. Geneva accepts, but Ken reconsiders after Mark inadvertently scares him about the seriousness of marriage.
Mark promises that he will introduce Tyler to his favorite rap star, who happens to be an old friend of Mark's. Nicole gets a makeover from Vanessa and Geneva.
While Vanessa's friends give her a pre-wedding party at a strip club where her old boyfriend works, Mark's buddies host a similar party for him.

Vanessa wonders if Mark really understands her. She places an ad in the personals section and then tests Mark by telling him to determine which ad is hers. Nicole and Tyler try to find a song to sing at the wedding.
